==[[Esperanto]]==
===Etymology===
Ending for nouns and object pronouns in Finnish (''[[tuo]]''), Italian (''[[amico]]'', ''[[quello]]''), Portuguese (''[[amigo]]''), Russian ([[то]]), Spanish (''[[amigo]]'', ''[[eso]]'', ''[[algo]]'')

===Suffix===
'''-o'''
# -thing, -person. ([[Nominal]] suffix. All Esperanto [[noun]]s end in ''-o''.)
#* ''[[amiko]]'': friendly '''person''', [[friend]]
#* ''[[patro]]'': parental '''person''', [[father]]
#* ''[[vorto]]'': verbal '''thing''', [[word]]
# -thing. ([[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlative]] object ending.)
#* ''[[kio]]'': which '''thing''', [[what]]
#* ''[[tio]]'': that '''thing''', [[that]]
#* ''[[ĉio]]'': all '''things''', [[everything]]
#* ''[[io]]'': some '''thing''', [[something]]
#* ''[[nenio]]'': no '''thing''', [[nothing]]

